              <table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="0">
                <tr>
                  <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#B62029" class="boxtitle"><p>Sky&rsquo;s the limit for showbiz Lisa</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td width="18%"><img src="../images/lisa conner-sml.jpg" alt="Lisa Conner" width="110" height="110" border="0"></td>
                  <td width="82%" bgcolor="#CBD3C6" class="bodytext"><p>A Leeds Trinity postgraduate  journalist is getting ready to mingle with the stars after landing a job as a  reporter with the Sky News showbiz team.</p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td colspan="2" class="bodytext">
                    <p>Lisa Conner will be based in  central London,  attending parties and premieres to get the inside story on all the celebs in  town. </p>
                    <p>Her new boss, Sky&rsquo;s showbiz  website editor Victoria Saggers, was a trainee on the Postgraduate Diploma in Bimedia  Journalism course in 2001.</p>
                    <p>Lisa will soon be filing  copy for the website at <a href="http://showbiz.sky.com/showbiz/home">http://showbiz.sky.com/showbiz/home</a>,  and she&rsquo;s delighted to be starting her job straight off the course.</p>
                    <p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a dream start to my career.  The brilliant training that I received at Leeds Trinity helped me secure the  position against many other candidates.<br>
                        <br>
  &rdquo;I believe one of the most important things at the start is getting hands-on 
                      experience. The great thing about the bimedia course is that you get to 
                      do everything - writing, editing, producing, reporting, presenting, live work 
                      and packaging.&nbsp; These are all skills that will stay with me throughout my
                      career in news - and got me that all important first job.&quot; </p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p class="bodytext">&nbsp;</p>
